{"doc_urls":["intro.html#mdbook-embedify","usage.html#installation","usage.html#syntax","ignore-embeds.html#ignore-embeds","global-configuration.html#global-configuration","third-party/intro.html#third-party-apps","third-party/gist.html#options","third-party/gist.html#example","third-party/youtube.html#options","third-party/youtube.html#example","third-party/bilibili.html#options","third-party/bilibili.html#example","third-party/codesandbox.html#options","third-party/codesandbox.html#example","third-party/stackblitz.html#options","third-party/stackblitz.html#example","third-party/codepen.html#options","third-party/codepen.html#example","local/intro.html#local-apps","local/scroll-to-top.html"],"index":{"documentStore":{"docInfo":{"0":{"body":12,"breadcrumbs":3,"title":2},"1":{"body":38,"breadcrumbs":2,"title":1},"10":{"body":8,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"11":{"body":3,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"12":{"body":12,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"13":{"body":4,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"14":{"body":12,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"15":{"body":6,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"16":{"body":19,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"17":{"body":7,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"18":{"body":18,"breadcrumbs":4,"title":2},"19":{"body":62,"breadcrumbs":4,"title":2},"2":{"body":27,"breadcrumbs":2,"title":1},"3":{"body":32,"breadcrumbs":4,"title":2},"4":{"body":40,"breadcrumbs":4,"title":2},"5":{"body":21,"breadcrumbs":6,"title":3},"6":{"body":8,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"7":{"body":3,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"8":{"body":8,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1},"9":{"body":3,"breadcrumbs":5,"title":1}},"docs":{"0":{"body":"Crates.io Crates.io This is a mdbook preprocessor plugin that allows you to embed apps to your book, like youtube, codepen and some other apps.","breadcrumbs":"Intro » Mdbook Embedify","id":"0","title":"Mdbook Embedify"},"1":{"body":"There are two ways to install this plugin. You can install it from crates.io using cargo. cargo install mdbook-embedify Or you can download the binary from releases page. But it only supports Linux and Windows , if you are using MacOS , you have to install it from crates.io. After installation, add the following code to your book.toml file: [preprocessor.embedify] And that's it! You can now use embed macro to embed apps to your book.","breadcrumbs":"Usage » Installation","id":"1","title":"Installation"},"10":{"body":"Option Description Required Default id Video ID Yes - -","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Bilibili » Options","id":"10","title":"Options"},"11":{"body":"{% embed bilibili id=\"BV1uT4y1P7CX\" %}","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Bilibili » Example","id":"11","title":"Example"},"12":{"body":"Option Description Required Default id Project ID Yes - - theme Iframe theme No dark","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Codesandbox » Options","id":"12","title":"Options"},"13":{"body":"{% embed codesandbox id=\"ke8wx\" theme=\"light\" %}","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Codesandbox » Example","id":"13","title":"Example"},"14":{"body":"Option Description Required Default id Project ID Yes - - theme Iframe theme No dark","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Stackblitz » Options","id":"14","title":"Options"},"15":{"body":"{% embed stackblitz id=\"vitejs-vite-y8mdxg\" theme=\"light\" %}","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Stackblitz » Example","id":"15","title":"Example"},"16":{"body":"Option Description Required Default user username Yes - - slug Project slug Yes - - height Iframe height No 600 theme Iframe theme No dark","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Codepen » Options","id":"16","title":"Options"},"17":{"body":"{% embed codepen user=\"MR-Addict\" slug=\"NWBOqKw\" height=\"600\" theme=\"dark\" %}","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Codepen » Example","id":"17","title":"Example"},"18":{"body":"Local apps are apps hosted on your local book, so it is not necessary to have internet connection to use them. Below are all supported local apps and its detailed options. Scroll To Top","breadcrumbs":"Local Apps » Local Apps","id":"18","title":"Local Apps"},"19":{"body":"Scroll to top button app has no options. You can use it like this: {% embed scroll-to-top %} This only works for chapter that embeds this, not for the whole book. Most of cases, you want to use it for the whole book. You can do this by adding scroll-to-top option to embedify preprocessor in book.toml file like this: [preprocessor.embedify]\nscroll-to-top = true 💥Attention When you do this, you don't need to add {% embed scroll-to-top %} manually. It will be automatically added it to every chapter. Otherwise, it will be rendered twice. This book uses this option. You can see it at the bottom right corner of this page. But it only shows when pages are long enough to scroll. Or you can see it my another book Notes .","breadcrumbs":"Local Apps » Scroll To Top","id":"19","title":"Local Apps"},"2":{"body":"The basic syntax is like this: {% embed app options[] %} options are key-value based array seperated by space and its value must be wrapped by quotes . For example: {% embed codepen user=\"MR-Addict\" slug=\"NWBOqKw\" height=\"600\" theme=\"dark\" %} You can see some examples at examples section.","breadcrumbs":"Usage » Syntax","id":"2","title":"Syntax"},"3":{"body":"Sometimes you may want preprocessors to ignore some embeds. You can do it by wrapping content that you want to ignore with below two comments: <!-- embed ignore begin --> <!-- embed ignore end --> For example: <!-- embed ignore begin --> {% embed youtube id=\"DyTCOwB0DVw\" %} <!-- embed ignore end --> And youtube embed won't be rendered.","breadcrumbs":"Ignore Embeds » Ignore Embeds","id":"3","title":"Ignore Embeds"},"4":{"body":"Some apps allow you to automatically add to every chapter. You can do this by adding app-name = true to embedify preprocessor in book.toml file to enable it. For example: [preprocessor.embedify]\nscroll-to-top = true 💥Attention When you do this, you don't need to add {% embed scroll-to-top %} manually. It will be automatically added it to every chapter. Otherwise, it will be rendered twice. Now scroll-to-top is the only app that supports global configuration.","breadcrumbs":"Global Configuration » Global Configuration","id":"4","title":"Global Configuration"},"5":{"body":"Third party apps are apps that are hosted on third party sites. Below are all supported third party apps and its detailed options. Gist Youtube Bilibili Codesandbox Stackblitz Codepen","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Third Party Apps","id":"5","title":"Third Party Apps"},"6":{"body":"Option Description Required Default id Gist ID Yes - -","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Gist » Options","id":"6","title":"Options"},"7":{"body":"{% embed gist id=\"76cf171d1bdd7da41d4ca96b908eb57a\" %}","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Gist » Example","id":"7","title":"Example"},"8":{"body":"Option Description Required Default id Video ID Yes - -","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Youtube » Options","id":"8","title":"Options"},"9":{"body":"{% embed youtube id=\"DyTCOwB0DVw\" %}","breadcrumbs":"Third Party Apps » Youtube » Example","id":"9","title":"Example"}},"length":20,"save":true},"fields":["title","body","breadcrumbs"],"index":{"body":{"root":{"6":{"0":{"0":{"df":1,"docs":{"16":{"tf":1.0}}},"df":0,"docs":{}},"df":0,"docs":{}},"a":{"d":{"d":{"df":3,"docs":{"1":{"tf":1.0},"19":{"tf":1.0},"4":{"tf":1.4142135623730951}},"i":{"c":{"df":0,"docs":{},"t":{"df":2,"docs":{"17":{"tf":1.0},"2":{"tf":1.0}}}},"df":0,"docs":{}}},"df":2,"docs":{"19":{"tf":1.4142135623730951},"4":{"tf":1.4142135623730951}}},"df":0,"docs":{},"l":{"df":0,"docs":{},"l":{"df":0,"docs":{},"o":{"df":0,"docs":{},"w":{"df":2,"docs":{"0":{"tf":1.0},"4":{"tf":1.0}}}}}},"n":{"df":0,"docs":{},"o":{"df":0,"docs":{},"t":{"df":0,"docs":{},"h":{"df":1,"docs":{"19":{"tf":1.0}}}}}},"p":{"df":0,"docs":{},"p":{"df":7,"docs":{"0":{"tf":1.4142135623730951},"1":{"tf":1.0},"18":{"tf":2.0},"19":{"tf":1.4142135623730951},"2":{"tf":1.0},"4":{"tf":1.7320508075688772},"5":{"tf":2.0}}}},"r":{"df":0,"docs":{},"r":{"a